      "role": "user",
      "content": "but you just said it yourself, it's all just an inevitable strike of death anyway. if the logic holds that everything is temporary and ends in nothing, then the struggle itself is just unnecessary friction. if someone is already in pain, and there's no ultimate point to the suffering, isn't it actually more \"rational\" to just stop fighting it? why is \"staying afloat\" considered the right choice when the tide is clearly just going to take everything eventually?",
